{"title":"If Adam Picked the Apple","link":"https://kottke.org/24/10/if-adam-picked-the-apple","date":1729875523000,"content":"\n        <p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/rebuke-adam-eve.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/rebuke-adam-eve.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/rebuke-adam-eve.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"935\" alt=\"a painting of God rebuking Adam for tasting the apple and Adam in turn blaming Eve who in turn blames the snake\" /></p>\n\n<p>From <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/daniellecoffyn/\">Danielle Coffyn</a>, a poem called <a href=\"https://thenorthmeridianreview.org/blog/if-adam-picked-the-apple-and-other-poems\">If Adam Picked the Apple</a>. Hereâ€™s the first bit of it:</p>\n\n<blockquote><p>If Adam Picked the Apple</p>\n\n<p>There would be a parade,<br />\na celebration,<br />\na holiday to commemorate<br />\nthe day he sought enlightenment.<br />\nWe would not speak of<br />\ntemptation by the devil, rather,<br />\nwe would laud Adamâ€™s curiosity,<br />\nhis desire for adventure<br />\nand knowing.</p></blockquote>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://thenorthmeridianreview.org/blog/if-adam-picked-the-apple-and-other-poems\">You can read the rest of the poem here</a> and <a href=\"https://daniellecoffyn.substack.com/p/book-announcement\">preorder her poetry collection of the same name</a>.</p>\n\n<p>BTW, the hilarious painting is <a href=\"https://www.nga.gov/collection/art-object-page.111718.html\">The Rebuke of Adam and Eve (1626)</a> by Domenichino. That Adam, what a wanker.</p>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/art\">art</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Danielle%20Coffyn\">Danielle Coffyn</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/Domenichino\">Domenichino</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.o